OL,3,CWater bills to rise by an average of
OL,4,C#31 a year over next five years
OL,6,FSome water companies have been allowed
OL,7,Fto increase prices significantly.
OL,8,FSouthern Water customers will face a
OL,9,F53% increase and Severn Trent
OL,10,Fhouseholds will see their bills rise
OL,11,Fby 47%, before inflation.
OL,13,FThis comes as around 60,000 people in
OL,14,FSouth Hampshire are without water for
OL,15,Fa second day running following a fault
OL,16,Fat a Southern Water supply works.
OL,18,FMeanwhile, Thames Water has been
OL,19,Fhanded an #18.2 million penalty for
OL,20,Fbreaking dividend payment rules, Ofwat
OL,21,Fsaid.
