OL,3,CWater bills to rise by an average of
OL,4,C#31 a year over next five years
OL,6,FEnvironment Secretary Steve Reed said
OL,7,F"the public are right to be angry" and
OL,8,Fblamed the previous Tory government
OL,9,Ffor the state of the water industry.
OL,11,FHe said: "Under the Conservatives, our
OL,12,Fsewage system crumbled. They
OL,13,Firresponsibly let water companies
OL,14,Fdivert customers' money to line the
OL,15,Fpockets of their bosses and
OL,16,Fshareholders.
OL,18,F"The public are right to be angry
OL,19,Fafter they have been left to pay the
OL,20,Fprice of Conservative failure.
