OL,3,CWater bills to rise by an average of
OL,4,C#31 a year over next five years
OL,6,F"Customers will be hit particularly
OL,7,Fhard from April, with a large chunk of
OL,8,Fthese increases frontloaded into next
OL,9,Fyear ` on top of inflation.
OL,11,F"We know at least two in five
OL,12,Fhouseholds will find these increases
OL,13,Fdifficult to afford, but the support
OL,14,Fbeing offered by some water companies
OL,15,Flacks ambition.
OL,17,F"The case for a single social tariff
OL,18,Fto end the current postcode lottery of
OL,19,Fsupport has never been more
OL,20,Fcompelling."
